1
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:04,600
Davros. My name is Davros.

2
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:06,800
DOCTOR: Davros created
a new kind of warrior.

3
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:08,440
Davros made the Daleks.

4
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:09,960
But who made Davros?

5
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:11,800
DAVROS: You said you'd help me!

6
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:13,720
Shame. You're ashamed.

7
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,120
COLONY SARFF: Davros is dying.

8
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,960
He has a message for the Doctor.

9
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,040
This is a trap!

10
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:19,160
(HISSING)

11
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:20,240
You brought me to Skaro!

12
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:21,800
MISSY: This is the planet of the Daleks.

13
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:25,800
Clara!

14
00:00:25,880 --> 00:00:28,200
You cannot help her now, Doctor.

15
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:31,640
Compassion is wrong.

16
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:38,680
(ROPE CREAKING)

17
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:45,240
Consider the Doctor.

18
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:49,080
The Doctor, trapped. The Doctor, alone.

19
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:52,760
-You all right there, dear?
-Where are we?

20
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,680
-How did we...
-MISSY: Shh, now, Mummy's talking.

21
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,680
OK, I'm going to tell you
a story of the Doctor.

22
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:01,840
It's classic.

23
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:04,040
On the run, no Tardis.

24
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:08,720
No friends, no help.

25
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,320
In other words, the Doctor happy.

26
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,720
It was a long time ago.

27
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,440
Doesn't matter which
face he was wearing,

28
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:17,040
they're all the Doctor to me.

29
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,560
So let's give it to the eyebrows.

30
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,120
But the Daleks?

31
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,560
Yes, I'm coming to that.

32
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:25,080
Shouldn't we be, um...

33
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:27,840
-I don't want to say dead?
-Hush!

34
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:31,000
-He's travelling by teleporter.
-(BEEPING)

35
00:01:31,080 --> 00:01:32,960
Unfortunately, his teleporter
ls out of power.

36
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:35,040
Also unfortunate, he's being stalked by,

37
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:37,640
oh, say about 50 android assassins.

38
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:40,960
I may be rounding up.

39
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:42,640
Ow!

40
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:46,600
Fifty invisible, indestructible
android assassins.

41
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:49,120
All exclusively programmed to kill him.

42
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,720
Why are you sharpening that stick?

43
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:53,720
Well, I have no idea how long we're
going to be stuck out here,

44
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,640
might have to go hunting.

45
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,120
So why am I tied up?

46
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,680
In case there is nothing to hunt.

47
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,760
(CHUCKLES)

48
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,520
The Doctor then, surrounded,

49
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,640
outnumbered, outgunned.

50
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:10,080
And freeze.

51
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:13,920
Nanoseconds to live.
Four, I'd say, being generous.

52
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,320
Now, my question is this,

53
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:21,320
how did he survive?

54
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,160
Oh, come on, Clara.

55
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,480
You know him.

56
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,040
Consider the Doctor.

57
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:36,120
(CHUCKLES)

58
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,440
(BEEPS)

59
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,240
Where did he get that teleport thingy?

60
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:41,960
Oh, good. Good!

61
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,360
He stole one from an android.

62
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:45,120
So, I'm guessing

63
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,120
he uses the same energy
as the android weapons, right?

64
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,520
Excellent!

65
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:52,040
-Not seeing you as sandwiches now.
-OK then.

66
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,320
He uses the energy wave
from the android weapons

67
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,840
to recharge the teleport bracelet,

68
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:58,120
and at the exact moment
he's supposed to disintegrate,

69
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,200
he actually teleports.

70
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,840
Hang on! That's how you did it.

71
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,440
(SCREAMS)

72
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,440
That's how we escaped the Daleks.

73
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,520
I modified the same principles

74
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:11,000
for our vortex manipulators, yes.

75
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:13,280
Blew them off, I'm afraid.

76
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,160
But the Doctor, he improvised it.

77
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,800
He must have got through
several thousand calculations

78
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:20,400
in the time it takes
to fire up a disintegrator.

79
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:22,800
Seriously, what a swot!

80
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:26,040
CLARA: So the androids think he's dead
and the Doctor escapes.

81
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,600
MISSY: No, he's the Doctor.

82
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,720
He fell into a nest of vampire monkeys.

83
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,640
(MONKEYS SCREACHING)

84
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:37,240
But that's another story.

85
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,320
(GRUNTS)

86
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:44,080
Why does the Doctor always survive?

87
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,040
Because he's clever!

88
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,680
Yes, but there's lots of
clever dead people.

89
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:50,200
I love killing clever-clogs.
They make the best faces.

90
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,920
Because he always assumes
he's gonna win.

91
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,560
He always knows
there is a way to survive,

92
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:06,000
he just has to go and find it.

93
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:08,080
Yes, except this time, he made a will,

94
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,800
and threw himself a goodbye party.

95
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,800
Now, if the Doctor assumes
he is going to die,

96
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:12,960
what happens then?

97
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,800
We do.

98
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,680
He's trapped at the heart
of the Dalek empire.

99
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,160
He's a prisoner of the creatures

100
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,520
who hate him most in the universe.

101
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,000
Between us and him is everything

102
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:28,560
the deadliest race in all
of history can throw at us.

103
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:32,880
We, on the other hand,
have a pointy stick.

104
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,440
How do we start?

105
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,640
We assume we're gonna win.

106
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,000
Oh, pity really.

107
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:43,320
I was actually quite peckish.

108
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,960
-Can I have a stick, too?
-Make your own stick.

109
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,640
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

110
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:34,240
DAVROS: It took me so long
to realise it was you,

111
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:37,520
standing at the gates of my beginning.

112
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:41,200
And here you are at the end.

113
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:45,520
But this time, I have you at my mercy.

114
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,920
Exterminate!

115
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:50,240
Doctor?

116
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:55,600
Ancient, inoperable.

117
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,000
(GUN POWERS UP)

118
00:05:58,280 --> 00:06:00,040
Genius.

119
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:02,680
You would threaten a dying man?

120
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,000
Have I not suffered enough?

121
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:06,520
Get out.

122
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:09,440
I cannot leave this chamber.
It sustains me.

123
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,840
Get out!

124
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:16,280
DALEK 1: Alert! Alert!
The infirmary is breached.

125
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,880
SUPREME DALEK: Protect Davros.

126
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,600
Davros must be assisted.

127
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:23,200
DALEK 1: Davros is
leaving the infirmary.

128
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:25,600
SUPREME DALEK: Davros must remain.

129
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,840
Davros cannot leave.

130
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:31,400
DAVROS: My children, help me!

131
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:34,000
SUPREME DALEK: You
must return to the infirmary.

132
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:36,840
DAVROS: The Doctor is escaping.

133
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:39,240
Find him! Find the Doctor!

134
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,800
SUPREME DALEK: Find the Doctor.

135
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:44,760
Seek, locate, destroy.

136
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:45,880
DALEX 2: Locate.

137
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,160
DALEK 3: Destroy.
DALEK 4: Seek.

138
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,240
DALEX 2: Locate.

139
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,000
DALEK 5: Exterminate the Doctor.

140
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,360
DALEK 6: Exterminate the Doctor.

141
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,480
Exterminate.

142
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:55,200
CLARA: What's happening?
MISSY: What do you think?

143
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,120
He's in the middle of that.

144
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,400
Ah, that's what we need!

145
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:04,760
DALEKS: Exterminate! Exterminate!

146
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,640
DAVROS: Assist me.

147
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,680
DALEK 1: Davros approaches.

148
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:13,520
SUPREME DALEK: Admit Davros.
Admit the creator.

149
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,080
DAVROS: (STRAINING) Help me!

150
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,800
SUPREME DALEK: Assist Davros! Assist!

151
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:22,160
(DAVROS WHEEZING)

152
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:33,200
Admit it. You've all had
this exact nightmare.

153
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:37,760
Get me Sarff!

154
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,640
COLONY SARFF: I am here.

155
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,240
So, anyone for dodgems?

156
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,840
SUPREME DALEK: Exterminate!

157
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,480
DALEKS: Exterminate!

158
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:54,240
Daleks have sewers?

159
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:56,520
With one significant difference.

160
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,600
Being?

161
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,960
They are ever so slightly alive.

162
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,360
They're what?

163
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:03,240
How much of a drop
would you say that is?

164
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,440
Can you see the bottom?

165
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,800
It's too dark. Um...

166
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,360
We could chuck a stone down,
or something.

167
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:09,840
Oh, yeah, good idea.

168
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,000
(GRUNTS)

169
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:12,280
(SCREAMING)

170
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:15,320
-(THUDS)
-Twenty feet.

171
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:25,200
Of course, the real question is,

172
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,400
where did I get the cup of tea?

173
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:31,360
Answer, I'm the Doctor, just accept it.

174
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:34,080
SUPREME DALEK: You are unharmed.

175
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,440
Proposition,

176
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:38,560
Davros is an insane, paranoid genius

177
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,560
who has survived among several billion

178
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,600
trigger-happy mini tanks for centuries.

179
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:45,040
Conclusion, I'm definitely
having his chair.

180
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:47,400
SUPREME DALEK:
You cannot escape, Doctor.

181
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,000
(GUN COCKING)

182
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:52,240
I am guessing that
his personal force field

183
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,920
only works in one direction.

184
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,880
SUPREME DALEK:
The Doctor does not use weapons.

185
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,720
DOCTOR: Doesn't he?

186
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:02,120
Ah, listen to your little hearts beat!

187
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:08,040
What?

188
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,040
Hello.

189
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:18,320
Oh, poppet.

190
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,000
Do you really think you could?

191
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,200
First chance I get.

192
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:23,000
MISSY: You won't survive
down here on your own.

193
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,560
You won't survive turning your back.

194
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:28,240
Oh, how exciting!

195
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:37,280
God, you're dull!

196
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:42,080
In future, if you're
gonna take my stick,

197
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:45,240
do me the courtesy
of actually killing me.

198
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,800
Teamwork is all about respect.

199
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:50,160
-We're not a team.
-Of course we are.

200
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:52,560
Every miner needs a canary.

201
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,480
Now hush, look around.

202
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,480
Bit of a mess, isn't it?

203
00:09:58,560 --> 00:09:59,560
Well, you said it was a sewer.

204
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:04,080
The Daleks don't generate
much in the way of waste.

205
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,400
So what is it all, then?

206
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,480
Decaying Daleks.

207
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:08,960
Daleks can't die.

208
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:11,480
Genetically hard-wired
to keep on living,

209
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,480
whatever happens.

210
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:14,560
Well...

211
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,520
But they still age, poor loves.

212
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:20,480
Over time the body breaks down,

213
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,080
rots, liquefies.

214
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:28,040
Interestingly, the Dalek word for sewer

215
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,080
is the same as their word...

216
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:34,360
-(DECAYING DALEK SQUEALS)
-...for graveyard.

217
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:37,680
(DECAYING DALEKS SQUEALING)

218
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:38,960
Ask me what I want.

219
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,600
SUPREME DALEK: Irrelevant.

220
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,800
You will not prevail.

221
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:45,680
You will not succeed.

222
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:48,680
I've been at the heart
of your empire for 42 minutes,

223
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,880
and I own it,

224
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,640
and I haven't even
got out of my chair.

225
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:53,120
Ask me what I want.

226
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,400
SUPREME DALEK: What do you want?

227
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,360
Clara Oswald.

228
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,320
(OVER LOUD SPEAKER)
I want Clara Oswald.

229
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:04,560
Safe, alive,

230
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:08,480
and returned to me immediately.

231
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:12,880
You bring her back! You do that!

232
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,120
You do that now!

233
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,000
Unharmed.

234
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:19,800
Unhurt. Alive.

235
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,160
SUPREME DALEK: Your associate...

236
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:24,240
I saw what happened. I was there.

237
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:26,800
And I am hoping, for all of our sakes,
that it was trick.

238
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:29,240
SUPREME DALEK: It was not a deception.

239
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:33,280
Because if Clara Oswald is really dead,

240
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:37,600
then you better be very,
very careful how you tell me.

241
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:39,440
Listen to that.

242
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:41,760
The Doctor without hope.

243
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,200
DOCTOR: Who's going to tell me?

244
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,800
Who's gonna go first?

245
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,640
Nobody is safe now.

246
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:49,920
DOCTOR: All the power
Davros had is mine.

247
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,240
Everything he had, I have.

248
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:57,120
Who is going to tell me
Clara Oswald is really dead?

249
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,600
He'll burn everything. Us, too.

250
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:03,320
SUPREME DALEK:
Clara Oswald is not alive.

251
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:09,960
DAVROS: Doctor,
this urge for conquest...

252
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:13,360
It is gratifying to see you learn.

253
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,880
Davros! You're up.

254
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,400
Sorry, this seat's taken.

255
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:20,440
Indeed. Oh, but not by you.

256
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:22,400
-(SNAKES HISSING)
-(SHUDDERING)

257
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:28,080
You've met my head
of personal security, I think.

258
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:30,360
Colony Sarff.

259
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:33,040
-His agents are everywhere.
-(GRUNTS)

260
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:39,040
DAVROS: Are you ready?
COLONY SARFF: Of course.

261
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:42,800
Be subtle, Colony Sarff.

262
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:47,040
Tonight we entrap the Time Lord.

263
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,320
What is that? A lift?

264
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:57,280
What? Never mind the Llift.
See that thing on the wall?

265
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,320
-What about it?
-Take a look.

266
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:02,760
-What is it?
-Closer.

267
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:05,440
-What am I even looking for?
-Nothing.

268
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:06,800
I'm giving it a good look at you.

269
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:10,280
DALEK: Intruder alert! Intruder alert!

270
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:12,440
-Intruder alert!
CLARA: Why the hell did you do that?

271
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:15,920
-Ever ring a doorbell and run away?
-Humanoid detected in lower level!

272
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,320
But not this time.

273
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,160
Daleks to lower level 13.

274
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,560
What the hell did you do that for?

275
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,720
We need to trap and kill a Dalek.

276
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:24,880
You are the bait, I am the hook.

277
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:28,560
Dark star alloy,

278
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:31,920
goes through arm our plating
like a knife through people.

279
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,280
Missy. Missy.

280
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:35,120
Missy, uncuff me now!

281
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,720
It's pretty, though, isn't it?

282
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:39,560
Got it in the olden days of Gallifrey,

283
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:41,480
and the Doctor gave it to me
when my daughter...

284
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:42,640
(LIFT OPENING)

285
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:45,240
Keep it talking. We need
to draw it out of the lift.

286
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:48,440
You can't kill a Dalek with a brooch.

287
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,520
Yes, you can.

288
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,520
DALEK: Humanoid detected.

289
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,280
Remain still. Do not move.

290
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:57,520
Scan in progress.

291
00:13:57,600 --> 00:14:02,800
Humanoid unauthorised
in restricted area.

292
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:06,600
Sterilisation proceeding.

293
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,040
MISSY: Hey, you!

294
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:11,520
Guess what? I just put a hole in you.

295
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:15,960
And another. And another. And another.

296
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,680
What are you doing?

297
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:20,000
Murdering a Dalek.
I'm a Time Lady. It's our golf.

298
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,600
DALEK: Damage levels insignificant.

299
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:23,680
MISSY: Oh, really?

300
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:25,240
I think you're forgetting
you're surrounded

301
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:27,680
by a bunch of very old,
very angry Daleks.

302
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:28,760
(DECAYING DALEKS SQUEALING)

303
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:32,240
MISSY: (IN US ACCENT) You just got
a puncture in a bad neighbourhood.

304
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,200
Meet the locals,
all blind and squelchy,

305
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:37,280
and out of their tiny minds,
but they can still smell!

306
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,240
Nobody hates like a Dalek.

307
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,520
Here they come!

308
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:43,640
I think they want to steal your motor.

309
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:47,680
DALEK: (GURGLING) Emergency! Emergency!

310
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:51,040
My vision is impaired!
Exterminate! Exterminate!

311
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:53,320
MISSY: Oh, here comes
the older generation.

312
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:58,160
Oh, young folks today are so tetchy!

313
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:02,200
Emergency! Emergency!

314
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:04,200
(EXPLOSION)

315
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:09,280
YOUNG DAVROS: Help me.

316
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:15,400
You can't leave me.
You promised. You did!

317
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:20,600
You said I could survive,
you said you'd help me!

318
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,000
Help me!

319
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:26,680
(BEEPING)

320
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:34,440
DAVROS: I hope you are grateful.

321
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:36,880
It wasn't easy to procure.

322
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:40,640
And very nearly unique, of course.

323
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,760
You should feel privileged.

324
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:50,760
The only other chair on Skaro.

325
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:54,120
-Don't get up.
-You neither.

326
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,600
The chamber is sealed,

327
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:59,680
and I believe you are not
carrying your sonic device.

328
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:03,160
Gave it up. Bad memories.

329
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:07,200
I am dying, Doctor.

330
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,600
DOCTOR: You keep saying that.
You keep not dying.

331
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:12,200
Can you give it some welly?
Come on!

332
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:14,240
And it is time for us to conclude

333
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:16,680
our business together.

334
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,240
We have no business.

335
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:20,800
DAVROS: We have nothing but.

336
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:25,120
Look again at the cables, Doctor.

337
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:30,080
Understand what they are.

338
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:33,480
What they can do.

339
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:37,040
Just step a little closer.

340
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:53,400
(SNIFFING)

341
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:58,080
Get in.

342
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:04,120
They don't have much
respect for you, do they,

343
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:06,800
your kids?

344
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:09,320
Have you seen the state of this place?

345
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:12,040
I mean, this is exactly where you'd dump

346
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:14,120
a smelly old uncle,

347
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:18,800
slash family pet,
slash genius scientist

348
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,480
who couldn't even invent legs.

349
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,520
Seriously, how do your boys take it

350
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:24,520
when everybody else has got two eyes?

351
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,680
You know what it is, of course.

352
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:29,680
Oh, yes, it's a hyperspace relay

353
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:32,040
with some kind of a genetic component.

354
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:34,400
I am connected to the life force

355
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:37,320
of every Dalek on this planet.

356
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,200
It is what has kept me alive.

357
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:43,880
As their hearts beat, so does mine.

358
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:46,000
Ooh!

359
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,760
Nice!

360
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,120
Vampiring off your own creations,

361
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,640
just to eke out your days.

362
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:54,840
I'm surprised that the Daleks allow it.

363
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,920
Oh, they have no choice.

364
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,600
My Daleks are afflicted
with a genetic defect.

365
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,600
What defect?

366
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,280
Respect.

367
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:08,440
Mercy for their father.

368
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:14,680
Design flaws I was unable to eliminate.

369
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,280
And now he sees it.

370
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:23,920
Now he understands.

371
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:27,280
The cables, Doctor, touch them.

372
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:31,360
Imagine, to hold in your hand

373
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:36,080
the heartbeat of every Dalek on Skaro.

374
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:40,200
They send me life.

375
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:42,560
Is it beyond the wit of a Time Lord

376
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:45,880
to send them death?

377
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:50,320
A little work, and it could be done.

378
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,520
Now, why would you be telling me this?

379
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:56,000
Genocide in a moment.

380
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:02,880
Such slaughter, not in self-defence,

381
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:05,880
not as a simple act of war,

382
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:08,360
genocide as a choice.

383
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:12,400
Are you ready, Doctor?

384
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:17,360
So many backs with a single knife.

385
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:19,120
(DOCTOR SHUDDERING)

386
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:26,240
DAVROS: Are you ready to be a god?

387
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:44,000
Why do you hesitate?

388
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:47,040
No one would know.

389
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:49,120
Clara Oswald is dead.

390
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:58,160
Is this the conscience of
the Doctor or his shame?

391
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,520
The shame that brought you here.

392
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:03,200
There's no such thing as the Doctor.

393
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:08,000
I'm just a bloke in a box,
telling stories.

394
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:10,160
And I didn't come here
because I'm ashamed.

395
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:13,040
A bit of shame never hurt anyone.

396
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:17,240
I came...

397
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,320
...because you're sick and you asked.

398
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:29,720
And because sometimes, on a good day,

399
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:33,320
if I try very hard,

400
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:37,560
I'm not some old Time Lord who ran away.

401
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:43,840
I'm the Doctor.

402
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,040
Compassion, then.

403
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:51,240
Always.

404
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:54,640
It grows strong and fierce in you,

405
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,840
like a cancer.

406
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,080
I hope so.

407
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,000
It will kill you in the end.

408
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,800
I wouldn't die of anything else.

409
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,680
You may rely on it.

410
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,920
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

411
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,200
(BEEPING)

412
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,920
How am I supposed to
make it go without pedals?

413
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,720
Telepathic control. Open wide.

414
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:22,160
I meant your skull. Never mind.

415
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:23,760
-(STATIC WHISTLING)
-Ow!

416
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:25,320
-Shh. Now, don't worry.
-Ow!

417
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:29,360
There's loads of nanotech repairing any
damage as the feed goes in.

418
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:32,320
-What about when it comes out?
-I've no idea. Nobody knows.

419
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:34,800
Anyway, to control the unit
you just have to think.

420
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:36,960
A novel idea for you, but let's try it.

421
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:39,840
Move forwards.

422
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:41,800
I don't know how to... (GASPS)

423
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,560
-You see?
-Huh!

424
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:46,680
How did I do that?

425
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,560
-Circle right.
-I can't.

426
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:50,600
Circle left.

427
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:53,400
There you go.

428
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,200
All right, this won't hurt a bit.

429
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:56,720
Hang on. No, Missy.

430
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,240
No, no, no, no.

431
00:21:58,320 --> 00:22:00,760
No, Missy. Missy, no, no, no.
Please, don't!

432
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,120
Don't, don't, don't, please!

433
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:05,960
You OK?

434
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:07,960
Fine, I think.

435
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,520
(DALEK VOICE) Fine, I think.

436
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:12,440
-OK.
-(DALEK VOICE) OK.

437
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,280
That's a bit weird.

438
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:15,840
(CHUCKLING) Just a bit.

439
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:18,800
OK. All right, shh, say your name.

440
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:21,520
-(DALEK VOICE) why?
-Just... Just say it.

441
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,760
Clara.

442
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:23,880
(DALEK VOICE) Dalek.

443
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:26,000
Say it again.

444
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:28,600
-Clara Oswald.
-Dalek. Dalek.

445
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:30,400
MISSY: One more time.

446
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:31,480
I am Clara Oswald.

447
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:32,800
-I'm Clara Oswald.
-(DALEK VOICE) I am a Dalek.

448
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:33,880
I am a Dalek.

449
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:35,760
I am a Dalek! I am a Dalek!

450
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,320
(MISSY EXCLAIMS)

451
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:39,360
MISSY: Just...

452
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,720
Just don't get emotional.
Emotion fires the gun.

453
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:43,800
OK?

454
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:46,840
-I don't understand.
-(DALEK VOICE) I do not understand.

455
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,080
Say...

456
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,720
"I love you."

457
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:54,880
Those exact words.
Don't ask me why, just say it.

458
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:57,680
I love you.

459
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:59,880
-(DALEK VOICE) Exterminate.
-(CACKLING)

460
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:04,960
Say, "You are different from me."

461
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:06,960
-You are different from me.
-(DALEK VOICE) Exterminate!

462
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:09,040
Exterminate!

463
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:12,760
Say, "Exterminate.”

464
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,840
-Exterminate.
-(DALEK VOICE) Exterminate.

465
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,400
Exterminate! Exterminate!

466
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:22,480
(MISSY LAUGHING)
-Exterminate! Exterminate!

467
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:27,080
Exterminate!

468
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:30,080
Cybermen supress emotion.

469
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:32,680
Daleks channel it through a gun.

470
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:34,160
That's why they keep
yelling "Exterminate,”

471
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:36,120
it's how they reload.

472
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:41,840
So let's go and kill them. Come on.

473
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:46,200
There is a question, Doctor,
one I have longed to ask.

474
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:49,360
Yeah, well, if you're gonna put your
hand on my knee, it isn't gonna go well.

475
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:51,400
Why did you leave Gallifrey?

476
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:53,920
Well, because I did.

477
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:57,280
You stole a Tardis and ran and ran.

478
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,480
Why?

479
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:01,520
It was a boring place, Gallifrey.
I was going out of my mind.

480
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,520
Yet you long to return.

481
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,240
Ah, well, I'm inconsistent.

482
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:08,160
But it is always the same lie.

483
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:11,400
-What lie?
-You weren't bored.

484
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:15,720
No one runs the way you have
run for so a small reason.

485
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:17,640
I do.

486
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,480
No, you don't.

487
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:26,400
Colony Sarff confiscated
these items on your arrival.

488
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:29,920
A Time Lord confession dial, I believe.

489
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:32,760
Your confession.

490
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:34,600
Tell me.

491
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:39,360
Send me to my grave
with this precious knowledge.

492
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:43,040
What is the Doctor's confession?

493
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:44,480
Don't you dare!

494
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:47,600
Is it possible I have touched a nerve?

495
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:50,760
Some things matter
to me, Davros. Not many, but a few.

496
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:53,320
And you don't put your
fingers anywhere near them.

497
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:58,080
And they better not be scratched.
These are my best ones.

498
00:24:58,160 --> 00:25:00,800
DAVROS: Still you play the fool.

499
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:03,040
Well, by now,
that should make you nervous.

500
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:05,960
DALEK 1: Halt!

501
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:07,800
Report!

502
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,200
Humanoid intruder...

503
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:14,080
(DARLEK VOICE) Humanoid intruder
found on lower levels.

504
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:17,880
DARLEK 1: Why has the intruder
not been exterminated?

505
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:20,760
Explain!

506
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,120
Explain! Explain!

507
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:27,880
I'm a prisoner of special significance.

508
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,080
Count the hearts.

509
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:32,000
You are a Time Lord.

510
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:34,560
Time Lady, thank you.

511
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:37,120
Some of us can afford the upgrade.

512
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:40,000
Is it still the same old
Supreme Dalek these days?

513
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:43,640
I fought him once on
the slopes of the netherworld.

514
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:46,240
Tell him the bitch is back.

515
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:48,720
DAVROS: Make your confession, Doctor.

516
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:51,240
Why did you really leave Gallifrey?

517
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:54,520
How long has it been, you and I?

518
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:56,760
Long enough.

519
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,160
Galaxies have burned.

520
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:01,520
And now you ask me a personal question?

521
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:05,240
You have slaughtered
billions of my children,

522
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:09,160
as I have slaughtered
billions of your race.

523
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:13,880
We have exhausted
the conventional means of communication.

524
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:16,080
My people are alive.

525
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:18,400
They didn't die.

526
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:20,240
I brought them back. I found a way.

527
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:22,800
Is this true?

528
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:26,000
Gallifrey is back in the sky.

529
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:29,160
I don't know where, I may never know.

530
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:32,920
But Gallifrey is back and it is safe.

531
00:26:34,360 --> 00:26:35,560
From both of us.

532
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:38,920
DAVROS: Doctor,

533
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:44,160
my most sincere congratulations.

534
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:47,520
(SCOFFS) I'm sorry?

535
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,080
This is wonderful news.

536
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,520
Beyond all hope.

537
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:56,080
I congratulate you.

538
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:57,760
Why are you saying that?

539
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,960
A man should have a race,

540
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:03,240
a people, an allegiance.

541
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:06,480
A man should belong.

542
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:10,520
Doctor, believe me, please...

543
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,360
I am happy for you.

544
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:17,400
So happy.

545
00:27:17,480 --> 00:27:19,720
I don't... I don't understand this.
Why are you...

546
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:31,720
DAVROS: Come closer again.

547
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,560
Let me see your face.

548
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,240
You've seen it often enough.

549
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:38,760
Let me see it again,

550
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:42,760
with my own eyes.

551
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,080
(BEEPING)

552
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,800
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

553
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,400
Closer.

554
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:12,000
Please.

555
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:29,680
If you have redeemed
the Time Lords from the fire,

556
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:34,760
do not lose them again.

557
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:40,720
Take the darkest path
into the deepest hell,

558
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:45,360
but protect your own,

559
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:49,320
as I have sought to protect mine.

560
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:59,400
Did I do right, Doctor?

561
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:03,720
Tell me.

562
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:07,200
Was I right?

563
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:12,920
I need to know,

564
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:14,320
before the end,

565
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:18,320
am I a good man?

566
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:21,840
You really are dying, aren't you?

567
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:24,640
(INHALES DEEPLY)

568
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,120
Look at me.

569
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:29,280
Did you doubt it?

570
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,960
Yes.

571
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:37,640
Then we have established one thing only.

572
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:39,320
What?

573
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:45,920
You are not a good doctor.

574
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,760
(CHUCKLES)

575
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:57,440
(BOTH LAUGHING)

576
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:13,680
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

577
00:30:15,600 --> 00:30:16,840
(GROANS)

578
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:19,400
Pity.

579
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:22,600
I had hoped to see the sun

580
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:25,720
one last time,

581
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:28,240
with the eyes of my true self.

582
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:37,520
Oh, hello! (SCOFFS)

583
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:39,920
Look at you all,
with your nice shiny domes.

584
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:43,880
Oh! I am loving this.

585
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:46,120
You're my secret favourite,
don't tell the others.

586
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:48,960
SUPREME DARLEK: You are an enemy
of the Daleks.

587
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:52,760
Yes, well anyone who's not a Dalek
is an enemy of the Daleks,

588
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:55,240
so that was an easy guess.

589
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:57,520
You will be exterminated.

590
00:30:57,600 --> 00:31:00,560
Please, please do because
I have been on my feet all day.

591
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:04,040
But before you get all 'exterminatey',

592
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:05,400
two things.

593
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,880
One, I want to see Davros.

594
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:10,960
Two, I have a lovely
little gift for you all,

595
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:12,880
if you take me to him right now.

596
00:31:12,960 --> 00:31:15,520
We do not negotiate.

597
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:17,560
Clara Oswald.

598
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:22,600
I've brought you complete control
of the Doctor, gift-wrapped.

599
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:24,360
Better!

600
00:31:25,040 --> 00:31:26,240
Canned.

601
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:33,880
DAVROS: It is beautiful,
my world, is it not?

602
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:35,960
DOCTOR: How did you get it back?

603
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:38,920
The Daleks remade it.

604
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:43,400
(CLEARING THROAT) Like you,
they have a strong concept of home.

605
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:45,800
No, like you.

606
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:49,440
Everything you are, they are.

607
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:53,280
Hmm, like both of us, perhaps.

608
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:57,480
How far we have come to go home again.

609
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:06,320
I'm trying to pep this up,
but you've been gone a long time.

610
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:09,800
Every Dalek on Skaro
isn't enough any more.

611
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:13,560
It is so good of you to help me.

612
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,400
I'm not helping you.

613
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:18,640
I'm helping a little boy
I abandoned on a battlefield.

614
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:21,160
I think I owe him a sunrise.

615
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:27,480
-Come on, chin up.
-(GROANS)

616
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:29,560
Any minute now.

617
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:33,600
I have always admired you, Doctor.

618
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:35,280
Here it comes.

619
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,200
I wish,

620
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:40,000
just once,

621
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:44,160
we had been on the same side.

622
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,400
Look, the sun's coming up.

623
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:00,320
We're on the same side now.

624
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:06,040
I regret...

625
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,720
I cannot...

626
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,040
Open my eyes.

627
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:14,880
(SOBBING QUIETLY)

628
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,000
OK.

629
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:25,680
Don't ever tell anyone that I did this.

630
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:33,800
A little bit of regeneration energy.

631
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:36,640
Probably cost me an arm
or a leg somewhere down the line.

632
00:33:36,720 --> 00:33:39,120
Or I'll just be really little.
(CHUCKLES)

633
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:47,440
(DAVROS LAUGHS)

634
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:50,960
Should be enough, just to...

635
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:53,080
(SCREAMING)

636
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:56,160
Hold him firm, Colony Sarff.

637
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:58,840
He is precious to us now.

638
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:00,720
(GROANING)

639
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,320
DOCTOR: What are you doing?

640
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:05,640
Regeneration energy,

641
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:09,880
the ancient magic of the Time Lords.

642
00:34:10,720 --> 00:34:14,640
I thought I would have to tear you apart
to take it from you,

643
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:16,640
but as always,

644
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:20,840
your compassion is your downfall.

645
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:22,880
(GROANING)

646
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:24,000
No, please, no!

647
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:28,760
You have opened your veins
of your own free will,

648
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:33,000
and all Daleks shall
drink the blood of Gallifrey.

649
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:37,600
They shall rise stronger than ever.

650
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:39,840
(SCREAMING)

651
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:42,400
Where is Clara Oswald?

652
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:45,920
You will tell us! You will tell us/

653
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:47,720
You will tell us/

654
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:50,680
(DARLEKS POWER DOWN)

655
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,480
I'm sorry, was I, um...

656
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,840
Was I boring you?

657
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:04,000
No, no, no, no, Doctor,
what have you done?

658
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:06,560
-What's happening?
-(IN DALEK VOICE) What is happening?

659
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,520
I have to find the Doctor.

660
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:11,000
-No! No!
-(IN DALEK VOICE) Exterminate!

661
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:12,480
Exterminate!

662
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:15,280
-(IN DALEK VOICE) Exterminate!
-You can't just leave me here.

663
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:19,680
There was a prophecy, Doctor,
on your own world.

664
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:22,320
(PANTING) I must... I must stop this.

665
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:24,200
I must stop this!

666
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:27,240
It spoke of a hybrid creature.

667
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:30,400
Two great warrior races

668
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,120
forced together

669
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:36,760
to create a warrior greater than either.

670
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:41,320
Is that what you ran from, Doctor?

671
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:44,480
Your part in the coming of the Hybrid?

672
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:46,480
Half Dalek,

673
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:49,400
half Time Lord.

674
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:53,240
-(DOCTOR SCREAMING)
-Give me your gun!

675
00:35:54,320 --> 00:35:55,480
Stop!

676
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:57,680
(SCREAMING)

677
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:12,040
(HISSING)

678
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:30,120
We are renewed.

679
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:33,200
We are more powerful.

680
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:36,720
The experiment has succeeded.

681
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:38,880
All praise Davros!

682
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:41,160
DALEKS: (CHANTING) All praise Davros!

683
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:43,640
All praise Davros!

684
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:45,800
All praise Davros!

685
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:48,440
All praise Davros!

686
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:56,320
Morning.

687
00:36:57,240 --> 00:36:59,760
-Where's Clara?
-MISSY: Oh, hello to you, too.

688
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,920
You're alive, so she is too,
where is she?

689
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:04,400
I'm fine, thanks for asking.

690
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:07,360
Oh, you are not fine.

691
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,760
Thanks to you, Doctor,

692
00:37:09,840 --> 00:37:14,080
my creations shall grow
to yet greater supremacy,

693
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:17,280
and my own life is prolonged.

694
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:22,080
This is the final defeat
of the Time Lords.

695
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,640
Have you nothing to say, Doctor?

696
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,480
Three!

697
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:32,000
Do you understand what has happened?

698
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:34,400
Hear my children sing.

699
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:36,480
Two!

700
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:39,680
Ooh, I know that face.

701
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:41,520
All praise Davros!

702
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:45,800
Creator, and saviour, of the Daleks.

703
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,080
-One!
-(CRASH)

704
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:53,000
What is that?

705
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:54,840
(CRASH)

706
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:57,880
What's happening?

707
00:37:58,400 --> 00:38:01,200
We are under attack/

708
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,520
Explain!

709
00:38:02,840 --> 00:38:04,000
Explain!

710
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:07,600
I knew exactly what you were doing,
and I let you do it.

711
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:10,960
You transmitted regeneration energy
into every Dalek on this planet.

712
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:12,640
Every single one.

713
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:14,560
What have you done?

714
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:18,080
One word. No, two words
actually. Uh, first word...

715
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:19,960
Moron.

716
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:21,480
(SNIGGERS)

717
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:24,200
Second word. Sewers.

718
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:30,000
DALEK: We have emergency!
What is happening?

719
00:38:30,080 --> 00:38:32,880
Our power is fluctuating!

720
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:33,960
No!

721
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:37,680
This cannot be correct!

722
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:39,880
How can this be?

723
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:43,080
Generations of Daleks
just woke up, very cross

724
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:45,440
and they are coming up the pipes!

725
00:38:45,800 --> 00:38:48,480
Or to put it another way, bye!

726
00:38:50,120 --> 00:38:52,480
Doctor, you must help me!

727
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:56,240
Can I just say it's been an
absolute pleasure to finally meet you.

728
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:58,760
(GROANS)

729
00:38:59,240 --> 00:39:00,600
Doctor!

730
00:39:03,040 --> 00:39:04,280
(GROANS)

731
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:12,080
DALEK 1: My vision is impaired.

732
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:13,360
I cannot see.

733
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:15,640
DALEK 2: Alert! I cannot control.

734
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:18,880
DALEK: Doctor!

735
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,760
This city is about to be
sucked into the ground.

736
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:23,040
Your own sewer is about to consume you.

737
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:25,040
There's no way you can win,
there is nothing you can do.

738
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:27,720
So just tell me, where is Clara Oswald?

739
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:30,080
I am a Dalek.

740
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:31,920
Yes, you're a Dalek. Where is Clara?

741
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,840
I am a Dalek.

742
00:39:33,920 --> 00:39:37,360
Yes, I know that you're a Dalek.
Where is Clara Oswald?

743
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:40,600
It's me! I'm right here, it's me!
I'm in here, it's Clara!

744
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:42,560
(DALEK VOICE) I am a Dalek.

745
00:39:42,640 --> 00:39:44,240
I am a Dalek.

746
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:45,640
Doctor, stop!

747
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:49,320
MISSY: It's you, isn't it?

748
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:52,600
No, I mean, no offence,
you all look alike, but it is you?

749
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:54,640
Yes, it's me, it's me. I'm right here.

750
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:56,480
Affirmative.

751
00:39:58,560 --> 00:40:00,600
Clara's dead, Doctor.

752
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:02,560
This is the one that killed her.

753
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:04,800
Do not listen to her.

754
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:07,640
I am a Dalek. I am a Dalek.

755
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:11,080
I got her out of the city, but this one
caught us and shot her down.

756
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:12,560
There was nothing
I could do, I'm afraid.

757
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,320
I am a Dalek.

758
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:18,480
She ran. She screamed.
I'm so glad you didn't have to see that.

759
00:40:18,560 --> 00:40:21,360
I am a Dalek. I am a Dalek.

760
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:23,120
This one's mad one, isn't it?

761
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:25,920
I mean it's almost, like,
like it's proud.

762
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:28,360
I am a Dalek. I am a Dalek.

763
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,760
I am a Dalek.

764
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:30,880
Kill it, Doctor.

765
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,360
They're all going to die anyway.

766
00:40:32,920 --> 00:40:34,400
Indulge yourself., go on.

767
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:36,720
Kill the Dalek.

768
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:40,000
Do not kill me! Do not kill me!

769
00:40:40,160 --> 00:40:41,600
Is Clara dead?

770
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:42,840
No!

771
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:45,640
Doctor, no. I'm not dead,
I'm in here! Can you hear me?

772
00:40:45,720 --> 00:40:47,520
I am a Dalek.

773
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:49,480
I am alive.

774
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:51,440
I'm your friend. I'm your friend!

775
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:54,240
I am your enemy. Your enemy...

776
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:56,360
No, please, don't.

777
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:58,520
DALEK: Mercy. Mercy.

778
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:02,120
You shouldn't be able to say that.

779
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:03,600
Mercy.

780
00:41:04,080 --> 00:41:06,000
That word shouldn't exist
in your vocabulary.

781
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:08,880
-How did Davros teach you to say that?
-Mercy.

782
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:13,280
Why aren't you trying to kill me?

783
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:14,760
Mercy.

784
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:17,120
Because I would never kill you.

785
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:20,080
You are the last person
I would ever kill.

786
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:24,160
I show mercy.

787
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:30,880
I'm putting the gun down.
Open your casing.

788
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:32,760
-How?
-How?

789
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:36,720
Just think the word "open,” it'll work.

790
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:39,040
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

791
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:50,160
Ah, look at that.

792
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:52,160
Now, there's a surprise.

793
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:54,600
Missy, run!

794
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:58,520
Doctor.

795
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:02,080
In a way, this is why I gave her to you
in the first place,

796
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:03,280
to make you see.

797
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:06,720
The friend inside the enemy.
The enemy inside the friend.

798
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:08,560
I'm sorry, Clara. I'm so sorry.

799
00:42:08,640 --> 00:42:10,120
MISSY: Everyone's a bit of both.

800
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:12,360
Everyone's a hybrid.

801
00:42:12,960 --> 00:42:14,240
I said run!

802
00:42:15,080 --> 00:42:17,360
It wasn't me who ran, Doctor.

803
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:19,200
That was always you.

804
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:26,160
(DECAYING DALEKS SQUEALING)

805
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:27,760
Emergency!

806
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,640
Dalek control is compromised.

807
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:35,280
Where was the Tardis?
It was over there somewhere, wasn't it?

808
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:37,120
SUPREME DALEK: What is happening?

809
00:42:37,200 --> 00:42:38,920
Explain! Explain!

810
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:41,360
Dalek Supreme,
your sewers are revolting.

811
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:50,720
You will assist or you
will be exterminated.

812
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:52,800
Ah, well, go on then, exterminate away!

813
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:54,200
Doctor!

814
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,240
Oops, sorry.

815
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:01,120
Tardis force field's still here.

816
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:02,880
We get in, you don't.

817
00:43:02,960 --> 00:43:05,120
The Tardis has been destroyed!

818
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:07,440
Oh, don't be silly, of course it hasn't.

819
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:09,960
It's just redistributed
itself for a moment.

820
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:12,080
Hostile Action Dispersal System.

821
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:14,000
I'll just give it a quick
blast from my sonic,

822
00:43:14,080 --> 00:43:16,120
and the real time envelope
will reassemble right here.

823
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:17,920
Doctor, you don't have your screwdriver.

824
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:19,920
Oh, yeah, I'm over screwdrivers.

825
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,440
They spoil the line of your jacket.

826
00:43:21,520 --> 00:43:25,600
These days, I'm all about
wearable technology.

827
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:26,960
CLARA: No!

828
00:43:27,040 --> 00:43:28,240
No.

829
00:43:28,320 --> 00:43:29,320
Seriously?

830
00:43:33,160 --> 00:43:35,120
SUPREME DALEK: What is happening?

831
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:37,280
Ah, same old, same old.

832
00:43:37,360 --> 00:43:40,560
Just the Doctor
and Clara Oswald in the Tardis.

833
00:43:44,920 --> 00:43:45,920
(WHOOSHING)

834
00:43:47,160 --> 00:43:48,360
(GRUNTS)

835
00:43:52,040 --> 00:43:54,080
Humanoid detected.

836
00:43:54,160 --> 00:43:56,320
Humanoid detected.

837
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:58,000
Remain still.

838
00:43:58,080 --> 00:44:00,200
Do not move. Do not move.

839
00:44:00,280 --> 00:44:01,600
You are a Time Lord!

840
00:44:02,480 --> 00:44:03,880
(GRUNTING)

841
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:10,320
You know what?

842
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:13,600
I've just had a very clever idea.

843
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:17,560
(EXPLOSIONS IN DISTANCE)

844
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:27,400
No chance you're going to tell me what's
in that confession dial, I suppose?

845
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:28,920
(CLARA CHUCKLES)

846
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:32,440
Doesn't make sense.

847
00:44:32,840 --> 00:44:33,880
What doesn't?

848
00:44:33,960 --> 00:44:36,240
When you were in the Dalek,
you made it say "mercy."

849
00:44:36,320 --> 00:44:38,360
It shouldn't have
understood the concept.

850
00:44:38,840 --> 00:44:40,040
It shouldn't have been able to say it.

851
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:45,200
How did a tiny piece of mercy
get into the DNA of the Daleks?

852
00:44:59,440 --> 00:45:00,440
Doctor?

853
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:06,840
YOUNG DAVROS: Help me!

854
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:13,120
You can't leave me, you promised.

855
00:45:13,560 --> 00:45:15,000
You said I had a chance.

856
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:16,320
(WHOOSHING)

857
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:20,200
Who are you?

858
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:23,160
I don't get it.

859
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:25,600
How did you get there?

860
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:27,120
From the future.

861
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:30,280
Are you going to save me?

862
00:45:30,880 --> 00:45:33,120
I'm going to save my friend,

863
00:45:33,200 --> 00:45:34,480
the only way I can.

864
00:45:34,560 --> 00:45:36,600
-(COCKS GUN)
-Exterminate!

865
00:45:53,720 --> 00:45:54,720
Come on.

866
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:56,640
I'll take you home.

867
00:45:57,400 --> 00:45:58,760
DAVROS: Which side are you on?

868
00:45:59,640 --> 00:46:01,080
Are you the enemy?

869
00:46:09,320 --> 00:46:11,440
I'm not sure that any of that matters,

870
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:12,760
friends, enemies.

871
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:17,320
So long as there's mercy.

872
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:20,960
Always mercy.

873
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:50,800
CLARA: I want another adventure.

874
00:46:50,880 --> 00:46:52,680
Monsters, things blowing up.

875
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:55,280
DOCTOR: Be careful what you wish for.

876
00:46:58,360 --> 00:47:00,520
We are fighting
an unknown homicidal force.

877
00:47:00,600 --> 00:47:03,040
Underwater, in a nuclear reactor.

878
00:47:03,640 --> 00:47:06,440
Everything I think it couldn't
get more extraordinary, it surprises me.

879
00:47:07,440 --> 00:47:08,840
They can walk through walls.

880
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:11,560
They only come out at night.

881
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:14,960
It's impossible. I hate it!

882
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:16,920
It's evil. It's astonishing.

883
00:47:17,080 --> 00:47:18,800
-Who the hell are you?
-The Doctor!

884
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:21,800
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

